Create play images:
http://www.poornerd.com/2014/10/10/yes-it-is-now-this-easy-to-dockerize-a-play-framework-application/

In play app folder:
sbt docker:publishLocal
docker run -p 9000:9000 requesthandler:1.0-SNAPSHOT
docker run -p 8080:9000 webcrawler:1.0-SNAPSHOT

sudo docker run -p 9000:9000 --name request_api --link db:db requesthandler:1.0-SNAPSHOT
sudo docker run -p 8888:8888 --name webcrawler --link db:db webcrawler:1.0-SNAPSHOT


Build MongoDB image:
https://docs.docker.com/examples/mongodb/

Run MongoDB
docker run -p 27017:27017 --name mongo_instance_001 -d my/repo

docker run -d --name db my/repo
docker run -d -p 27017:27017 --name db my/repo
on server
docker run -d -p --name db -i -t my_mongodb


Build WebApp in docker
http://rdn-consulting.com/blog/2014/11/29/publishing-a-static-angularjs-application-with-docker/#Creating_an_AngularJS_application

In DockerFile
# Build myapp server Docker container
FROM coreos/apache
MAINTAINER MyName
COPY app /var/www/

sudo docker build -t dockeruser/myapp .

sudo docker run -d -p 9001:80 --name my-app dockeruser/myapp /usr/sbin/apache2ctl -D FOREGROUND


CHECK IP OF CONTAINER:
docker inspect container_name | grep IPAddress

